      "title": "Classical Theory of Fields",
      "abstract": "A thin film circuit having a high reliability may be produced by depositing an electrically conductive thin film composed of tantalum, tantalum nitrides, niobium or hafnium on a substrate of an insulating material, and forming capacitors or resistors on the substrate from the deposited thin-film while oxidizing the portions other than these elements to change them into a non-conductive film."
